Queendora: Hey, what are you doing to our great hero?

Mandora Guard: Dora! Dora!!! La!!!

Sharice: Hey! Be careful!

Sharice: Uh, nope. Must be imagining things.
Sharice: Anyway, I got rid of all the monsters.
Good Student: My thanks, then! So, are you from around here? Are you familiar with the area?
Sharice: What's with the twenty questions?
Good Student: I'm actually studying Maple Lake's ecosystem, and I heard rumors that some strange organisms grow around here.
Good Student: I heard they look like big radishes, and they make a sound like "dora dora".
Good Student: People say eating them raw has a lot of health benefits. They could even cure diseases.
Sharice: (Eating them... raw!?)
Sharice: Ah... nope, I just came from over there, and I definitely didn't see anything.
Sharice: I bet it's all lies! People just want excuses to come ruin our natural environment!

Good Student: Oh really? Hmm... 
Yeah, I thought it all sounded a little too far-fetched, anyway. Thanks for you help.
Mandora: Doraaa? Dora?
Sharice: ...Huh?
Sharice: (Their kingdom's got monsters that eat them, but... outside it seems like there's even more to worry about.)
Mandora: Ola—Dora—
Puggi: Your Majesty, even if the great hero ran off,
Puggi: I'm the true main character here. I'll take care of that big ol' monster like yesterday's lunch!
Sharice: So that guy ended up bolting?

Puggi: Sharice~~
